The paper deals with machine learning algorithms applied to image analysis, specifically image saliency methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a general framework for learning different kinds of explanations for any black box algorithm, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations of current techniques and proposes a new method, which involves explicit and interpretable image perturbations, indicating that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of explaining black box algorithms, which is related to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
